On Thu, 21 Nov 2002 myangelmorgan(-at-)juno.com wrote:

> ...i forgot that the new CV boot came with a tube of grease, so
> when i was cleaning the joint that didnt need a new boot, i started
> packing it with grease... just not the stuff that came with the other
> boot. this stuff is blue and it is for bearings. do i need a special kind
> of grease for the CVs or is this grease ok?

Not a big problem.  just pull the boot back, wipe as much of the incorrect
grease out as you can, then pack with the correct stuff.  A little of the
incorrect grease won't hurt.

Latex gloves and lots of paper towels make this job tolerable.

